{{Infobox journal | title = The Bible and Critical Theory | cover = | former_name = | editor = Caroline Blyth, Robert J. Myles | discipline = [[Biblical studies]] | abbreviation = Bible Crit. Theory | publisher = | country = | history = 2004-present | frequency = Biannually | openaccess = Yes | license = [[Creative Commons Attribution 4.0]] | website = http://novaojs.newcastle.edu.au/ojsbct/index.php/bct/index | link1 = http://novaojs.newcastle.edu.au/ojsbct/index.php/bct/issue/current | link1-name= Online access | link2 = http://novaojs.newcastle.edu.au/ojsbct/index.php/bct/issue/archive | link2-name = Online archive | eISSN = 1832-3391 | LCCN = | OCLC = 76789239 }} '''''The Bible and Critical Theory''''' is a biannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[open access]] [[academic journal]] in the fields of [[biblical studies]] and [[critical theory]]. The journal operates as the premier venue for exploratory, interdisciplinary, and innovative work in biblical studies. It was established by Roland Boer in 2004, and was published by [[Monash University]] ePress until 2010. Since 2011 it has been published independently and hosted by the University of Newcastle.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Bible and Critical Theory |url=http://www.epress.monash.edu/bc/ |publisher=[[Monash University]] |accessdate=13 June 2016}}</ref> The incumbent [[editor-in-chief|managing editors]] (since 2016) are Caroline Blyth and Robert J. Myles.
