==South Hall== {{Main article|South Hall (UC Berkeley)}}
The School of Information is located in historic [[South Hall (UC Berkeley)|South Hall]]. Built in 1873, it is the oldest building in the University of California system. South Hall is located in the heart of campus, near the Doe Library and the Campanile (also known as [[Sather Tower]]). It is known to have the smallest bear statue on the Berkeley campus{{Citation needed|date=April 2007}}. The small bear was added by Michael H. Casey, who did the ornamental castings for the restored facade in 1997.<ref>{{cite book |title= The Campus Guides: University of California Berkeley |last= Helfland |first=Harvey | year=2001 |publisher=Princeton Architectural Press |isbn= 1-56898-293-3 |page=43}}</ref>
